  ---
  EXPLANATION

  Why tiered powers?
  - Basic (^1): Linear. 30 lines = 30. No punishment.
  - Deps (^7): 2 deps = 128. 3 deps = 2,187. Explodes
  fast.
  - Complex (^10): 2 risks = 1,024. 3 risks = 59,049.
  Nuclear.

  The effect: Higher C → Higher tier → More analysis
  forced before build.

  ---
  POWER REFERENCE
  ┌──────────────┬──────────────────┐
  │  ^7 (deps)   │  ^10 (complex)   │
  ├──────────────┼──────────────────┤
  │ 1^7 = 1      │ 1^10 = 1         │
  ├──────────────┼──────────────────┤
  │ 2^7 = 128    │ 2^10 = 1,024     │
  ├──────────────┼──────────────────┤
  │ 3^7 = 2,187  │ 3^10 = 59,049    │
  ├──────────────┼──────────────────┤
  │ 4^7 = 16,384 │ 4^10 = 1,048,576 │
  ├──────────────┼──────────────────┤
  │ 5^7 = 78,125 │ 5^10 = 9,765,625 │
  └──────────────┴──────────────────┘
  ---
  EXAMPLES
  Task: 10 basic, 0 deps, 0 complex
  C Calculation: 10 + 0 + 0
  C Value: 10
  Tier: Simple
  Allocation: 40/60
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Task: 10 basic, 2 deps, 0 complex
  C Calculation: 10 + 128 + 0
  C Value: 138
  Tier: Simple
  Allocation: 40/60
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Task: 10 basic, 2 deps, 1 complex
  C Calculation: 10 + 128 + 1
  C Value: 139
  Tier: Simple
  Allocation: 40/60
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Task: 10 basic, 3 deps, 1 complex
  C Calculation: 10 + 2187 + 1
  C Value: 2,198
  Tier: Medium
  Allocation: 75/25
  ────────────────────────────────────────
  Task: 10 basic, 4 deps, 2 complex
  C Calculation: 10 + 16384 + 1024
  C Value: 17,418
  Tier: Critical
  Allocation: 85/15

